%% Data Flow Diagram: Workload-Variant-Autoscaler (WVA)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant vLLM as vLLM Inference Servers
    participant Prom as Prometheus/Thanos Querier<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant SatEng as Saturation Engine<br/>(30s polling loop)
    participant Cache as Decision Cache<br/>(in-memory)
    participant Controller as VariantAutoscaling<br/>Controller
    participant Metrics as Metrics Endpoint<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant HPA as HPA / KEDA
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over vLLM,K8sAPI: Flow 1: Saturation-Based Autoscaling (30s interval)

    vLLM->>Prom: Emit vllm:kv_cache_usage_perc,<br/>vllm:num_requests_waiting
    SatEng->>Prom: PromQL Query<br/>Bearer Token (SA token)
    Prom-->>SatEng: Saturation Metrics
    SatEng->>SatEng: Analyze KV cache + queue depth<br/>Apply GPU limits
    SatEng->>Cache: Write VariantDecisions
    Cache->>Controller: Read decisions (Go channel)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update VariantAutoscaling status<br/>SA Token
    Controller->>Metrics: Emit wva_desired_replicas,<br/>wva_desired_ratio
    HPA->>Prom: Read wva_desired_replicas<br/>via prometheus-adapter
    HPA->>K8sAPI: Scale Deployment<br/>(scale subresource)

    Note over vLLM,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Scale-from-Zero (100ms interval)

    participant EPP as EPP Service<br/>(InferencePool)
    participant SFZEng as Scale-from-Zero Engine<br/>(100ms polling loop)

    SFZEng->>EPP: Query flow_control_queue_size<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    EPP-->>SFZEng: Queue metrics
    SFZEng->>K8sAPI: Scale 0→1 via scale subresource<br/>SA Token
    SFZEng->>Cache: Write decision
    Cache->>Controller: Read decisions
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update VariantAutoscaling status

    Note over vLLM,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Configuration Hot-Reload

    participant CM as ConfigMap<br/>(Kubernetes watch)
    participant CMCtrl as ConfigMap Controller

    CM->>CMCtrl: ConfigMap change event
    CMCtrl->>CMCtrl: Update in-memory config<br/>(thread-safe)
    Note right of CMCtrl: Saturation Engine reads<br/>updated config on next cycle
